# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PRIVATE FACILITATION CONTENT — never commit real sessions or learnings.
# The toolkit (practices/, templates/, agents, docs) is public and reusable.
# Your actual workshop designs, feedback, and lessons stay on your machine.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Ignore every real workshop folder…
/workshops/*
# …but keep the committed, sanitized example(s) that show newcomers the shape:
!/workshops/EXAMPLE-*/

# Ignore your aggregated lessons-learned…
/lessons-learned/*
# …but keep its explainer so the folder exists in a fresh clone:
!/lessons-learned/README.md

# Editor / OS noise
.DS_Store
*.swp
